                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.01/160: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-03T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 3, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 3—1:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4909. With reference to our telegram number 4820, August 28, 8 p.m., we
                    understand from the Foreign Office that Eden did suggest to General de Gaulle
                    that it would be well for him to return to London to talk over pending problems
                    but that de Gaulle does not seem willing to come back just now. De Gaulle merely
                    states that there are a number of matters pending which require his presence in
                    the Near East.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
